On 12/7/2011 2:46 AM, Lourd Baltimore wrote:
> The next time I
> change spark plugs, I'm going to use the old ones to make up some piston
> stops.
>
> Basically drill out the centers and epoxy in a dowel or some plastic
> pen tubes.

I'd use a bolt or steel rod of some sort with the end rounded.  Plastic 
or wood will give and you won't get a truly accurate reading.  Stopping 
the piston against a metal stop isn't going to hurt the pistons as long 
as your careful and rotate slowly.

Mike
